content.data:
Done. Here's the summary:

## Fix Applied

**Problem:** App crashes in background (release build) with stack overflow in `libflutter.so` when streaming songs fail.

**Root cause:** `_playOfflineByGenre` was calling `playSong()` with `await`, which in AOT/release builds caused a recursive stack overflow when called from error recovery paths (rate limit, audio URL empty, etc.).

**Fix:** Wrapped the `playSong` call in `_playOfflineByGenre` with `Future.microtask()` to break the synchronous call stack:
```dart
// Before
await playSong(offlineQueue.first, queue: offlineQueue);

// After
Future.microtask(() => playSong(offlineQueue.first, queue: offlineQueue));
```

**Why downloaded songs work:** They have local file paths (`/data/...` or `file://`), so no network fetch is needed and no error recovery path is triggered.

The fix is committed to `develop`. Want me to push?

input.oldStr:
  rlog('[MusicPlayerProvider] offline queue: ${offlineQueue.length} songs, first: ${offlineQueue.first.title}');
  // Use microtask to break synchronous call stack and prevent stack overflow in AOT
  Future.microtask(() => playSong(offlineQueue.first, queue: offlineQueue));
}

input.newStr:
  rlog('[MusicPlayerProvider] offline songs available: ${offlineQueue.length}, stopping playback');
  // Don't auto-play to avoid stack overflow in release builds
  // User can manually play downloaded songs
  await _audioHandler.stop();
  _currentSong = null;
  notifyListeners();
}

